    "Fig. 9 Examples of calculating Crowdedness in 2D and 3D environments.",
    "In a, the blue circles and the gray rectangles denote the agents and dynamic obstacles, respectively, and the gray-blue walls denote the static obstacles.",
    "In b, the drones and the birds denote the agents and dynamic obstacles, respectively, and the trees and building denote the static obstacles destination when computing the Success Rate.",
    "The Detour Percentage and Effective Velocity indicators are also susceptible to missing a critical aspect of an algorithm's robustness and reliability in real-world scenarios.",
